sp.p:
I gueſs the reſt, ah! you are a happy man, you are in love;
I wiſh I was in love or in liquor, then I ſhou'd have warmth enough in me
to brave the weather.

Alarm'd my lord! why, tho' I am naturally as brave as a lion;
yet I do not like to be taken thus by ſurprize; it is that which alarms
me—and Sir Palamede I am ſure is at the bottom of this.
